.Dd June 29, 2026
.Dt LAMBDASCRIPT 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm lambdascript
.Nd LambdaScript language overview
.Sh DESCRIPTION
LambdaScript is a lambda-calculus-oriented language with arithmetic, boolean logic, symbolic operators, set-membership syntax, quantified forms, and reduction tracing.
.Sh LANGUAGE FEATURES
.Bl -bullet
.It
lambda abstractions and application
.It
numeric literals and arithmetic
.It
boolean constants and connectives
.It
symbolic forms such as equivalence and implication
.It
quantifiers, summation, integral, and limit-style syntax
.It
set-membership forms
.It
official and user-defined imports
.El
.Sh REDUCTION
Evaluation is normal-order oriented and can be traced from the CLI.
.Sh IMPORTS
LambdaScript expands imports before parse and evaluation.
Duplicate imports are skipped and cyclic imports are rejected.
Official libraries are imported with brace syntax and user files with quoted paths.
.Sh OFFICIAL LIBRARIES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic Logic
Provides
.Ic NAND ,
.Ic NOR ,
and
.Ic XOR
in terms of built-in boolean operations.
.It Ic Vector
Provides a functional sequence API including
.Ic PUSH ,
.Ic HEAD ,
.Ic TAIL ,
.Ic MAP ,
.Ic FILTER ,
.Ic LENGTH ,
.Ic CONCAT ,
and
.Ic FOLD .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr lambdascript 1
